\\textbf{Evaluation of Blind Spot Correction}\\\\
\\vspace{0.1cm}
\\\\In order to calculate the Cut-off angle for our Blind-Spot-Correction, the angular statistics of the line segments in reconstructed image stacks were evaluated. The probability density is therefore plotted over the angle distribution of checked fibres (cf. Fig. ..........http://dl.dropbox.com/u/9670269/theta.gif....). One can see that from an orientation angle of \\frac{0.1}{\\pi} to the observation axis no fibres are visible in the evaluated stack. So \\omega is about $36\\,^\\circ$ which leads to a Cut-off angle of $72\\,^\\circ$ (cf. Fig. 6 in Claus big Appendix). With the angle \\omega, the correction factor for reflection mode stacks can be calculated:
\\begin{equation}
\\sigma_{corr}= \\sigma\\, \\sqrt{\\frac{\\omega}{2}}
\\end{equation}

